        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2966311497" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16434110498524143122">I had a professor in college that said the Pulitzer was the cheapest literary prize. &quot;All you have to do is wave an American flag and they&apos;ll give you a Pulitzer!&quot; I have no idea if he is right. I&apos;ve waved flags. Mostly those little ones you get at the Dollar Tree before the fourth of July. No one has given me a prize. <br/><br/>Anyway, Forrest Gander got a Pulitzer for this collection, (2019). I didn&apos;t spy any flag waving and this a solid collection of poem. Some of it quite moving as he wrestles in poem</span>
  <span id="freeText16434110498524143122" style="display:none">I had a professor in college that said the Pulitzer was the cheapest literary prize. "All you have to do is wave an American flag and they'll give you a Pulitzer!" I have no idea if he is right. I've waved flags. Mostly those little ones you get at the Dollar Tree before the fourth of July. No one has given me a prize. <br /><br />Anyway, Forrest Gander got a Pulitzer for this collection, (2019). I didn't spy any flag waving and this a solid collection of poem. Some of it quite moving as he wrestles in poems with his mother's Alzheimer's, grief over his wife, C.D. Wright's death, and his translation of St. John of the Cross. Some verse remain opaque to me but others I found quite moving!</span>
  <a data-text-id="16434110498524143122" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


