<div id="review_2806948381" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2806948381" />
    <a title="Anthony Conty" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/58891502-anthony-conty"><img alt="Anthony Conty" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2806948381?book_show_action=true">May 13, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Anthony Conty" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Anthony Conty" href="/user/show/58891502-anthony-conty">Anthony Conty</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2806948381" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14232787587303340435">Personal note: I haven&apos;t read anything since the surgery. My vision was blurry and I was reading when I started having symptoms and could not bring myself back to the book that reminds me of that.<br/><br/>&quot;Be With&quot; is this year&apos;s Pulitzer winner for poetry by Forrest Gander. He has a B.S. in Geology from William &amp; Mary and an M.A. in Literature from San Francisco State University. He writes like a geologist and you will need a dictionary.<br/><br/>Gander recently lost his partner and is losing his mother to Alzhei</span>
  <span id="freeText14232787587303340435" style="display:none">Personal note: I haven't read anything since the surgery. My vision was blurry and I was reading when I started having symptoms and could not bring myself back to the book that reminds me of that.<br /><br />"Be With" is this year's Pulitzer winner for poetry by Forrest Gander. He has a B.S. in Geology from William &amp; Mary and an M.A. in Literature from San Francisco State University. He writes like a geologist and you will need a dictionary.<br /><br />Gander recently lost his partner and is losing his mother to Alzheimer's. He also worked as a translator along the border. This adds up to tales of grief, loss, and regret. Some of the lines here will get to you.<br /><br />I cannot pick a favorite quote. "Ruth", the story of his mother's confused state, says, "Choose whatever you will and the disease still wins." In "Son", when he addresses his son about the death of his mother, he states, "I gave my life to strangers; I kept it from the ones I love."<br /><br />Admittedly, I did not understand all of these works, but a lot of them hit home. Better yet, most of them are available online. The man has seen some things and gone through some stuff. "For a loss that every other loss fits inside."</span>
  <a data-text-id="14232787587303340435" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


